Special thanks to thn81, L42y, City-Busz, and all of the other AUR maintainers that helped make it possible to run Unity under Arch Linux!

Please make sure you don't already have modified versions of the dependencies installed. For example, gtk3-ubuntu might fail to compile if there's a modified version of gtk3 already installed.

Packages ending with "-ubuntu" contain Ubuntu patches and REPLACE Arch Linux versions of those packages.

Order to compile/install:

01: glib2-ubuntu                   -> glib 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
02: libx11-ubuntu                  -> X11 client side library with Ubuntu patches
03: libxi-ubuntu                   -> X11 Input library with Ubuntu patches
04: gtk2-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
05: gdk-pixbuf2                    -> An image loading library
06: gtk3-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 3.0 with Ubuntu patches
07: qt-ubuntu                      -> Qt toolkit with Ubuntu patches
08: gconf-ubuntu                   -> A configuration database system
09: libdbusmenu                    -> Library for passing menus over DBus
10: libindicator                   -> Symbols and functions for indicators
11: libindicate                    -> Libraries for apps to raise 'flags' on DBus
12: libindicate-qt                 -> Qt bindings for libindicate
13: libappindicator                -> Library to export menu bar to Unity
14: appmenu-gtk                    -> Application menu module for GTK+
15: bamf                           -> Application matching framework
16: libqtbamf                      -> Qt bindings for bamf
17: dee                            -> Create Model-View-Controller apps over DBus
18: libqtdee                       -> Qt binding and QML plugin for Dee
19: libqtgconf                     -> Qt bindings for GConf
20: dconf-qt                       -> Qt bindings for DConf
21: sni-qt                         -> Turns Qt tray icons into appindicators
22: ido                            -> Widgets and objects used for indicators
23: libzeitgeist                   -> Client library to interact with Zeitgeist
24: zeitgeist-datahub              -> Plugins that insert events into Zeitgeist
25: geoclue                        -> Modular geoinformation service
26: python2-geoclue                 -> Geoclue Python module
27: python2-xapian                  -> Python bindings for Xapian
28: zeitgeist-extensions           -> Extensions for Zeitgeist
29: gnome-activity-journal         -> Tool for easily browsing and finding files
30: gsettings-desktop-schemas      -> Shared GSettings schemas for the desktop
31: gnome-desktop                  -> Library for various GNOME modules
32: gnome-settings-daemon-ubuntu   -> Daemon handling the GNOME session settings
33: gnome-session-ubuntu           -> GNOME Session Manager
34: pulseaudio-ubuntu              -> A featureful, general-purpose sound server
35: gnome-control-center-ubuntu    -> Utilities to configure the GNOME desktop
36: gnome-screensaver-ubuntu       -> Screensaver and screen locking for GNOME
37: metacity-ubuntu                -> Lightweight GTK+ window manager
38: launchpad-integration          -> Launchpad.net integration
39: mutter-ubuntu                  -> Lightweight GTK+ window manager
40: indicator-applet               -> GNOME panel indicator applet
41: indicator-application          -> Takes menus and puts then in the panel
42: indicator-appmenu              -> An indicator to host the menus from apps
43: libtimezonemap                 -> GTK+3 timezone map widget
44: indicator-datetime             -> A very, very simple clock
45: indicator-messages             -> Collects messages that need a response
46: indicator-multiload            -> Port of the GNOME multiload applet
