48: indicator-session              -> Indicator to manage session
49: indicator-sound                -> A unified sound menu
50: network-manager-applet-ubuntu  -> Network Manager applet with indicator support
51: gnome-bluetooth-ubuntu         -> Gnome bluetooth applet with indicator support
52: gtest                          -> C++ testing utility based on xUnit
53: gmock                          -> A library for writing C++ mock classes
54: overlay-scrollbar *            -> Overlay scrollbars for GTK 2 and GTK 3
55: plasma-widget-menubar *        -> KDE Plasma widget to display menubar
56: xfce4-indicator-plugin *       -> XFCE panel plugin to display indicators
57: xorg-xinput-ubuntu             -> Command line tool to configure input devices
58: mtdev                          -> Multitouch protocol translation library
59: utouch-evemu                   -> Event emulation for the uTouch stack
60: utouch-frame                   -> Touch frame library
61: fixesproto-ubuntu              -> X11 Fixes extension wire protocol
62: libxfixes-ubuntu               -> X11 misc. 'fixes' extension library
63: xorg-server-ubuntu             -> Xorg X11 server
64: check                          -> Unit testing framework for C
65: utouch-grail                   -> Gesture recognition and instantiation lib.
66: utouch-geis                    -> Implementation of the GEIS interface
67: nux                            -> An OpenGL toolkit
68: xf86-input-evdev-ubuntu        -> Xorg X11 evdev input driver
69: xf86-input-synaptics-ubuntu *  -> Xorg X11 Synaptics touchpad driver
70: unity-asset-pool               -> Design assets for Unity
71: gnome-menus2                   -> Gnome menu specifications
72: libunity                       -> Library for integrating Unity
73: libunity-misc                  -> Differently licensed stuff for Unity
74: nautilus-ubuntu                -> File manager and graphics shell for GNOME
75: unity-lens-applications        -> Unity applications lens
76: unity-lens-files               -> Unity files lens
77: unity-lens-music               -> Unity music lens
78: unity-lens-video               -> Unity video lens
79: compiz-core-ubuntu             -> Compiz core components
80: libcompizconfig-ubuntu         -> Compiz configuration system library
81: compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu * -> GConf backend for Compiz
82: compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu * -> KConfig4 backend for Compiz
83: compizconfig-python-ubuntu     -> Compizconfig bindings for Python
84: ccsm-ubuntu                    -> Compiz configuration manager
85: compiz-plugins-main-ubuntu     -> Compiz main plugins
86: compiz-plugins-extra-ubuntu    -> Compiz extra plugins
87: unity-core *                   -> Parts of Unity 3D needed for Unity 2D
88: unity                          -> A desktop experience designed for efficiency
89: unity-2d                       -> 2D implementation of Unity
90: unity-rotated-bzr *            -> A modified version of Unity (rotated)

* Optional packages
  - overlay-scrollbar              => For GNOME/Unity users who want a space saving scrollbar
  - plasma-widget-menubar          => For KDE users who want a global menubar
  - xfce4-indicator-plugin         => Ayatana indicators plugin for the XFCE panel
  - xf86-input-synaptics-ubuntu    => For users with a Synaptics touchpad (laptops)
  - compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in GConf
  - compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in KConfig4
  - unity-core                     => For users that want Unity 2D, but not Unity 3D
  - unity-rotated-bzr              => Modified Unity with the launcher at the bottom

All of PKGBUILD's were checked by namcap for consistency. The binary packages have not been checked yet.

Troubleshooting:

Global menus aren't working when logging in with KDM (KDE display manager).

  This happens because previous versions of KDM weren't patched to source the
  /etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc.d/ directory. This is fixed in kdebase-workspace version
  4.7.2-1, but requires the KDM configuration files to be regenerated (resetting
  all KDM configuration options). To regenerate the configuration files, run as root

    # rm -rvf /usr/share/config/kdm
    # genkdmconf
